-- Multiplus Poised for Four-Week High as Banco Santander Says Buy
-- B y   D e n y s e   G o d o y
-- 2012-09-12T17:03:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-12/multiplus-advances-to-four-week-high-as-santander-says-buy-1-.html
Multiplus SA, the frequent-flier
unit of  Latam Airlines Group SA (LFL) ’s Brazil subsidiary, headed for
a four-week high after  Banco Santander  Brasil SA recommended
buying the stock.  Shares advanced 2.9 percent to 45.27 reais at 1:52 p.m. in
Sao Paulo. A close at that level would be the highest since Aug.
15. The benchmark Bovespa index gained 0.5 percent.  In a report initiating coverage of the Sao Paulo-based
company, Banco Santander Brasil analysts including Henrique Navarro said Multiplus has a “unique” business model, is a
“cash cow company with high margins and returns,” and is
positioned for growth. The bank set a 53-real target price for
Multiplus by the end of 2013.  Multiplus gained 36 percent this year through yesterday,
while the Bovespa advanced 4.7 percent during that same period.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denyse Godoy in  Sao Paulo  at 
